<item>
            <title>[JXPATH-160] ValueUtils.getValue throws exception with set and index above size</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/JXPATH-160</link>
                <project id="12310480" key="JXPATH">Commons JXPath</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;ValueUtils offers a utility method to retrieve an indexed value from a collection. In case this collection is an array or a List, the method returns null if the index is above the size. If the supplied collection is a Set instead, then a NoSuchElementException is thrown if index is above size.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The desired behavior is that the result is the same for all kinds of collections and that even in the case of a Set null is returned if the index value is too large.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
